product-blueprint:

- RESOLVE is a settlement network, not a founder-operated analysis tool.
- Default path: users keep using GitHub/Navidrome/PeerTube/etc.; connectors observe; creators discover RESOLVE when they earn.
- First action is Connect an ecosystem — not paste a repository.
- Target nav: Home, Activity, Earnings, Connections, Account (user words).
- Creator-centric model: person → everything they create → everything owed — not repo → analyze → pay.
- Copy: Value exists → Money owes → Settlement fulfills. Not "founder funds → people get paid."
- Pause screen expansion until aligned with docs/PRODUCT-BLUEPRINT.md.
- Backend (ledger, connectors, settlement) stays; product UI must converge to blueprint.
